cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with click-through rate (CTR) prediction for native advertisements, which is a problem related to information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a recurrent neural network (RNN) model, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning (DL), making cs.CL and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses event embedding vectors, which can be seen as a form of feature engineering, and thus, cs.CV (computer vision) could also be a possible sub-category.
